##The first industry to go to zero in the wake of the epidemic

MICRO-SIGNAL YITIAOTV

Feature description, a short original video every day, every day to tell a moving story, every day selected human beauty, every day to live a better life with me.

Opening a bed and breakfast used to be a popular way to start a business,

But the sudden outbreak in early 2020,

But it's brought the industry almost to zero.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yu Feng Li bed-and-breakfast with red lanterns and couplets, its doors closed

We interviewed more than a dozen hosts,

Their stores are in Beijing, Nanjing, Taizhou, Hangzhou, Xiamen and overseas Japan,

Some people pay nearly $2 million a month in rent,

If there are no more orders, you won't last more than a month

Someone has invested $20 million in a store that is about to open,

Caught up in the face of rampant pneumonia, had to be dismissed on the spot staff.

An owner told A,

To hear other industries complain of being cut in half is envying,

Because the B & B is a direct result of zero.

City lodging brand in Beijing, Sanlitun and other hot spots have a number of housing, epidemic, rent pressure is huge

Rather than sit back and do nothing, bed-and-breakfast owners are doing everything they can to save themselves:

Small Business owners want to go back to work and subsidize their rent with their salaries,

Big brand short-term rent to long-term rent, and free and so on rent brand fight.

The consensus is:

In 2020, profit is a luxury,

Survival is the only goal.

Editor Yan Kunmu

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Aerial View of Yu Fung Lane bed-and-breakfast

"I saw the industry collapse. "

For Lodgings Entrepreneur Jin Xie, the New Year was supposed to be a hopeful one: His investment in high end lodgings, Yufengli, was finally about to start its first season.

Located in the Cultural Tourism District of Taizhou City, Linhai, Zhejiang Province, the project is a renovation of the century-old historic building "Yu Tong Feng" pawnshop and the 60-year-old warehouse complex. The renovation took four years, nearly $2 million in design alone, and the final cost of the renovation was $20 million.

In August 2019, the Typhoon Lekima made landfall and the sea is one of the worst hit areas in the country, flooding the city. Although the site is located at a high elevation, the store has half a meter of water in it, and books, furniture, appliances, and power supplies have been badly damaged. The renovation cost another one million.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jin Xie was in Yufengli after the typhoon passed

Before the Spring Festival, Yu Fengli was finally restored to business. After the Spring Festival, Jin Xie and his staff hung festive red lanterns and pasted window decorations in succession. Rooms online have been reserved out of 80% , which means that the long holiday, more than 30 rooms must be full, everyone thought finally experienced setbacks, endure a good harvest time.

Signs of trouble start around January 21st, when a handful of customers want to return their order. The night before, Academician Zhong Nanshan gave an interview to CCTV and made it clear that there was a human to human transmission of the new pneumonia. Fortunately, after all, there is a certain distance from the sea and Wuhan, the trip was affected by the guests or a small number.

A refund order from Yu Fung Lane

Unfortunately, the bad news didn't stop with optimism.

On January 23, Wuhan was officially closed down, and people all over the country began to realize the seriousness of the epidemic, and requests for return orders became more and more frequent. On the 24th, CTRIP announced that all of its hotel products would be returned without damage. On the same day, the local government issued a document requiring scenic spots, hotels and other related industries to close down.

In order to actively cooperate with this decision, without thinking and reaction, Jinxie and the shop assistant took the initiative to call the customer who had not cancelled the order and completed all the refunds. New Year's Eve, he dismissed more than 20 employees, leaving only one with him in the store on duty, so spent the most memorable New Year's.

Unlike Jin Xie, Davy runs an urban art bed and breakfast brand called Zhangsu, which operates more than 200 deluxe rooms in Beijing and Nanjing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The kitchen provides electrical appliances, kitchenware and condiments

Considering that the Spring Festival is mainly a family outing and the demand for kitchens is high, they have just bought a large number of kitchen appliances, kitchenware, tableware, and centralized renovation of the housing resources.

Most of the staff are outsiders, before the festival, Davy One by one and talk to everyone, to ensure that according to national regulations to pay three times salary, and worked out a detailed schedule, request everyone to stay. The cleaning ladies were outsourced and paid by the hour, but he promised to pay them double to avoid a shortage of workers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The four founders of the ring

Davy's partner, COVID-19, later recalled that he had seen news of the discovery as early as mid January. Bed-and-breakfast is a business that depends on the weather for its food. Erlong also has a vague concern about whether it will affect Nanjing, which is relatively closer to Wuhan. However, after talking with his peers, he found that everyone was relatively relaxed and believed that the epidemic would soon be brought under control, this Spring Festival won't be any different.

The change was also unexpected for the CEO, who documented it with clear data:

On 21 January, 50 cancellations were received and the operations department issued an exception alert.

On January 22, the UNSUBSCRIBE rate in Nanjing exceeded 40 percent, and in Beijing it exceeded 35 percent.

On January 24th, almost 80% of orders were cancelled.

On January 26th almost all orders were cancelled in February.

All orders that can be cancelled after February, January 27th..

During the year, the occupancy rate fluctuates periodically with the seasons and holidays, losing the peak season of the year, and it is almost certain that there will be no profit in the whole of 2020. To live is to win.

"I never thought about the destruction or the end of the urban bed-and-breakfast industry, " Erlong wrote in a self-written Essay. "Very lucky, or very unlucky. I witnessed the collapse of the industry. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The backend order cancellation record of the host

How much longer can you hold out?

Nor is life any better for those who are far from the epicentre of the epidemic than it is for those who close their shops. As mainland tourists cancel their travel plans, the scope of the problem is getting wider. A bed-and-breakfast in Kenting, Taiwan, has a occupancy rate of only 10% . The paper reservation register is filled with the reservation record covered by white correction liquid, but no new handwriting is filled in.

Ostay AIRBNB

Chinese visitors account for 40% of the more than 700 rooms operated in Japan by the overseas bed and breakfast brand, but their orders have fallen by half since February, as the country and Southeast Asia as a whole have become less willing to travel. The situation is similar for more than 200 bed-and-breakfast hotels in Thailand, where occupancy is down 30 per cent.

Interior view of the guest room at Yu Fung Lane

As a high end bed and breakfast in the scenic area, Yufengli's room rate fluctuates between 800 yuan and 1,600 yuan a night. For every day it is closed, it will lose about 40,000 yuan in turnover. By this rough calculation, it will lose one million yuan a month.

Words like "cold winter" and "cut in half" are no longer sufficient to describe the current situation of the lodging industry. "We are directly zeroed, " says Jin.

How much longer can you hold out? This is the first question every home-stay operator will ask themselves after properly handling the refund of the order.

The least risk-resistant stores opened in 2019. For them, the lease price at the time of signing is high, and a lot of money has been spent on upfront investment, which has not yet begun to flow back, all the reserves are low, can hardly bear any twists and turns. A home-stay host in Yangshuo turned to the Internet for help. He said he had invested more than 3 million yuan in opening a shop last year, more than 2 million of which were loans and loans, and that the pressure to repay the loans had become overwhelming.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Qi Qi's "children of the South" night scene

In 2018, Qi rented a house as a bed and breakfast in Weizhou Island, Guangxi's Beihai region. He is an independent owner of a bed and breakfast. After the closure of the island, public transport was interrupted, she was canceled five air tickets, a high-speed rail ticket, finally able to leave the island, back home to Chengdu. During this time, she even thought about whether to find a new job and subsidize her own store with her salary.

The West Lake bed-and-breakfast operators told one that their rents are comparable to those of the most high-end CBD office buildings in Hangzhou. In addition to fierce competition, the original profit is very thin, and will level off in 2019. It is already difficult to continue without income for half a month, now some of the owners are thinking about closing up shop. But more helpless is that the industry is at its lowest point, the prospects are not clear, even no one is willing to take over the transfer, only their own teeth continue to bear losses.

Davy gives us a more detailed account:

The average monthly rent for their apartment in Beijing is about 8,000 yuan per unit, and in Nanjing it is 4,000 to 5,000 yuan per unit. The rental cost alone is about 1.2 million to 1.5 million yuan per month. And years later is the peak period of rent renewal, many houses in the recent need to pay a quarter or even half a year's rent.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Handlebars

In addition, Internet charges, office rentals, warehouse rentals, online system maintenance and so on are fixed costs that are almost never reduced by occupancy, and every few days, a new bill is handed to him. Add in the extra expensive disinfectant, and zero-zero adds up to at least $2 million a month in operating capital, which means it would be hard for the company to survive for a month without doing anything.

What Davy fears more than financial losses is that the industry and consumers will lose faith in the industry through this campaign, and that this is a more permanent blow than the epidemic.

Eight cleaning ladies in a team of outsourcers who had decided to stay in Beijing years ago to double their salaries now have no work, no income, and no room and board. On the other hand, most of the country is closed off, can't even go home, "cried a lot, " Davy gives them temporary quarters, and tries to find work for them, for example, while it's empty, to the point of housing to do usually too late to do deep renovation and cleaning, for them to maintain basic living.

Guo Jielin, CEO of Ostay, has also had problems calming employees. At a time when news of the outbreak was most intense, her shop in Japan was receiving customers from Wuhan, causing panic among the cleaning staff. It wasn't until the guest explained in his travel records that he had left Wuhan before the siege and had been symptom-free for more than 14 days that he was able to calm down.

Save Yourself

After the outbreak, Zhu Wuxiang, a professor of finance at the School of Economics and management at Tsinghua University, sent questionnaires to 995 small and medium-sized enterprises, including those in the travel, hotel and bed and breakfast industries. The results showed that 34 percent of the enterprises could last only one month, 85% of businesses last up to three months.

Compared with the majority of small and medium-sized enterprises, home-stay is facing a more difficult prospect. This week, cities have clearly set a time for employees to return to work, and most will be able to resume production around February 10. However, residential accommodation is not a social necessity, and it will cause floating population to gather together, government notices in many areas read: "closed with immediate effect" and "opening hours will be announced later. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The founder of the "doctor's post" in Wuhan gives an interview to CCTV

For those who live in Hubei and other areas where the epidemic is serious, participating in the rescue of the epidemic is the first step of self-help. Around January 25, small-scale practitioners of the Wuhan Accommodation Industry set up an industry alliance, unified scheduling, free access to medical staff limited by commuting to stay.

The owner, Li Dan, was unable to return to Wuhan before the city was closed, but offered the combination to the door lock of her home hotel, which was checked in by a nurse from a nearby hospital, who brought her own bed linen and disinfectant, and repeatedly thanked her on wechat, she said she would take good care of the House and leave it as if no one had lived there.

However, the lack of room disinfection capacity, with the development of the epidemic, such a model has become difficult to continue. On January 30th Wuhan's bed-and-breakfast Alliance was disbanded to avoid cross-infection among its guests.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yinuo bed and stay in Changsha Guest Communication check-in

In Changsha, which is adjacent to Hubei Province, many travelers from Wuhan are stranded. Yi Nuo, a host, took the initiative to send a message on the Internet, offering 50 rooms to receive stranded Wuhan residents and medical staff free of charge. As there was no way to sterilize, so one room could only be checked in once, and once it was closed, it would no longer be used, after waiting for epidemic situation to do again unify again disinfect processing, contributed oneself to close before last energy.

Xiamen is far away from the epidemic area, and the local government has not forced the business owners to shut down, but only rules not to receive tourists from other places. But for businesses in this popular tourist destination, this still means losing all their guests. A bed and breakfast was fully booked before the 15th of the first month of the Lunar New Year, but it was all returned a year ago, adding to the monthly rent of 80,000 yuan and the salaries of eight employees, which cost the company one hundred thousand yuan.

Mr. Wang, the owner, had previously received a tour group from Hubei Province, voluntarily cooperated with the local work and went to the hotel isolation for 14 days. When he returned home unharmed, he decided to close the shop temporarily to stop his losses and sell items such as a goose down quilt and L'Occitane en Provence's washing kit at a discount on his friends'circle. As a local, he said this year's Spring Festival was the loneliest he had ever seen in Xiamen.

Tanimachi-san staff meet to discuss measures for the off-season

After the outbreak of the Tanimachi Airbnb in Japan, Kyoto stores were opened to stranded Chinese tourists at rock-bottom prices, initially to help their compatriots, but in February, the number of cancellations reached 50 percent, cutting prices became a way to save yourself. Usually sell 600 to 900 yuan of bed-and-breakfast accommodation down to 200 yuan a room, two-story single-family houses from 1200-3000 yuan down to 600 yuan a day, the maximum discount rate reached 20% , in CEO Liu Yang's words, "even cleaning fees are not enough, " but he thought he could not earn money, it's good to get some good reviews.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tanimachi-kun in the snow

After realizing that they were struggling to survive, the managing partner held a meeting quickly. The strategy was to change the short-term rent to long-term rent. The rent was charged only at cost. But Beijing's long-term rental market is highly competitive, leaving them little time to act. It can be expected that after the start of construction on February 10 is the peak in Beijing, comfortable, Xiangyu these mature brands will be in action at that time, decide their window of life and death period is only about 10 days.

On February 3, the hostel posted a letter on the Internet with a straightforward and even tragic title, asking for help: 200 sets of celebrity hostels for rent at limited time and at low prices.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A request for help from Hanjuku

After the news was sent out, the first group of prospective customers welcomed by the house, most of whom were also affected by the epidemic.

Some people were rework after the rental community to find their own half a month of isolation; a family should have lived in the new house at this time, but now decoration stagnation, had to rent a few months house transition. Recent graduates coming to Beijing to find work realize that there are few opportunities this year, that interviews will be a protracted battle, and that they need to settle down for a long time; the office building where a company is located is temporarily closed, find Their house and use it as temporary office space... During Special Times, an atmosphere of mutual assistance between the owner and the tenant goes beyond simple business dealings.

With the way of short-term rental to long-term rental, Hanzhu can solve about 20% of the housing resources. In addition, they also quickly screening out the rental expensive, low rental rate of housing, rental, hope to resolve 20% of the rental cost: "Some are breach of refund, pay breach of contract, yesterday we returned several sets. "

To further cut costs, Davy talks to some of its employees about taking unpaid leave of absence, and the company continues to pay their social security contributions. He knew this was not a long-term solution: "after all, if there is no income for a period of time, there is no reason for people to stay" , but for now, living is the biggest goal.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Davy sent a coded message to the staff

Waiting for hope

No one has a clear answer as to when the belt-tightening days will end. "after all, we can't talk about anything else until the epidemic is over, " he said

Both upstream and downstream industries have launched subsidies and bailouts for home-stay operators. CTRIP, AIRBNB and other platforms have set up related funds, and many owners in Sanya have announced three-month or even six-month rent reductions for bed and breakfast.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The local government in Taizhou has given Yufengli some preferential policies. For the time being, Jinxie does not have to worry too much about the rent. If the passenger flow after opening can not cover the operating cost, closing the shop and waiting is the safest option at present.

Even so, one can not be too optimistic about the future. Based on SARS data, Guo estimated that even if the epidemic had passed, tourists would have to wait and see for a month or so.

Liu Yang is worried that the cherry blossom season is over, and hopes that it will bounce back during the Tokyo Olympics, or the year will be over. The good news is that Japan has provided a lot of help to China in this outbreak, and he expects tourists to feel more favorable toward Japan.

Tanimachi-kun Japanese style bed and breakfast

"There is certainly no hope in three months, and it is now up to three to six months to recover, " says Davy, who has adjusted his mental outlook to mid-year, when he hopes to hit the summer peak. If not, had to come up with more housing conversion long rent, in order to obtain a stable cash flow, for this each house will lose about 5000 yuan per month income.

Running A bed-and-breakfast used to be a popular way to start a business, and in many people's minds, it represented a life free from triviality and the pursuit of poetry and distance. Kim Xie and Davy are typical entrepreneurs, both of whom have media experience prior to their careers, Kim Xie worked in television for six years, and Davy Uber for Internet companies. In 2016 and 2017, when they started, home accommodation was booming, but the flip side of that growth was that the bar wasn't very high, it was saturated in 2018, it was oversupplied in 2019, and Davy found that in the past year, everyone's overall turnover is down at least 10% or so.

In 2019 and 2020, Jin Xie once joked with a colleague, 2019 is almost no money, 2020 should rebound? I didn't expect a more devastating blow. But even without the outbreak, the industry has reached the point of culling, and the epidemic has only accelerated the process, practitioners said in an interview.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Reading space in Yu Fung Lane

There was hope in the crisis. After this setback, Jin Xie instead confirmed that he and his partners had chosen a high-end clientele, the boutique approach to design and service is the right one: "high-end customers, like people with 200 million in assets, even if they lose half and 100 million, he won't easily change his spending habits, but for the working class, even if he lost 5,000, he may not go out to play. "

Guo Jielin also believes that, practice is the most important thing for Ostay right now: "We are using our own Internet technology, we have some crowdsourcing systems, such as our sweepers are not our employees, are taking orders, we also have our own revenue management system, supply chain system online, provide a large-scale bed and breakfast solution. "

Davy also sees this period as a long-running "stress test" . Compared with such a single high-input project, Yufengli, how to achieve the standardized service as far as possible, but also with the same grade of the hotel has a distinction, make each store's characteristics, is a difficult point of survival. To this end, he and his partners want to optimize the company's asset management model: "This crisis is really a change in your perception, right? "? Adjust your perception, adjust your team, adjust your product. No one expects this to happen, so when it does, think about how I'm going to react to the next extreme."

Whether it is Yu Feng-li's defense as an attack, or the positive changes in the hands and feet, the effect of what, only wait time to verify.
